commands.name: az qumulo storage file-system create
commands.syntax:
az qumulo storage file-system create --file-system-name
                                     --resource-group
                                     [--admin-password]
                                     [--availability-zone]
                                     [--cluster-login-url]
                                     [--delegated-subnet-id]
                                     [--location]
                                     [--marketplace-details]
                                     [--mi-system-assigned]
                                     [--mi-user-assigned]
                                     [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                     [--private-ips]
                                     [--storage-sku]
                                     [--tags]
                                     [--user-details]

commands.name: az qumulo storage file-system delete
commands.syntax:
az qumulo storage file-system delete [--file-system-name]
                                     [--ids]
                                     [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                     [--resource-group]
                                     [--subscription]
                                     [--yes]

commands.name: az qumulo storage file-system list
examples: az qumulo storage file-system list -g rg

commands.name: az qumulo storage file-system wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
